# GaiaFTCL Fusion limb — plug-and-play plant architecture

Workspace may be **`FoT8D`** (monorepo root). Code under **`GAIAOS/`**.

## Multi-concept fusion (not tokamak-only)

Public taxonomy (magnetic confinement): **tokamak**, **stellarator**, **field-reversed configuration (FRC)**, **spheromak**, **magnetic mirror** (and variants). **Inertial confinement** (e.g. laser-driven laboratory implosion paths) is a **different plant class** with its own control/diagnostics surface. The **same GaiaFTCL operator app and mooring contract** applies across **which** facility concept and **which** vendor PCS stack is behind the bridge — **plug-and-play**, not a per-device forked UI.

## Plug-and-play PCS / plant I/O (same app)

Industry supplies **PCS**, central control, timing, and machine protection across fusion programs (e.g. open-control lineages such as **EPICS / CODAC-style** stacks in large facilities; integrators advertise fusion I&C and plasma control across **multiple experiments**). **Plant builders and control vendors** attach test bench, simulator, or live machine **without changing the Founder-facing app**: mooring, Fusion S⁴ console, wallet-gate path, DMG story stay **one surface**. Binding: **`GAIAOS/deploy/fusion_cell/config.json`**, **`GAIAOS/deploy/fusion_mesh/fusion_projection.json`**, **`bridges.*.invoke`**, site OPC/DAQ/SSH. **Not “mock”** — **interchangeable I/O backends**.

